column3: Automatic sanity-testing: PASSED, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/17121ec4fed58ec4a6f74c5ab4b4f9229619bd9a for binaries and test log.\n
So is this a compilation fix for Debian Squeeze, did I get that right? If yes I would say kick it in before 0.8 RC ;).\n

Yes, this helps compatibility with older Qt versions and is perfectly fine with me, I wish the debian folks would simply submit their changes as pull requests instead of sending a link with a list of patches though.\n
